Christine is a feminine name of Greek or  origin. It is derived from the word Christ, which is the Greek translation of the Hebrew word "Messiah". As a French variant of the Greek name Christina, it is a name in regular usage in French, English, German, Scandinavian, Dutch and  cultures, and it is often associated with the meaning "follower of Christ." Other ways to say Christine are Christina, , , , Kirsten, ,  (most used in Spain and Latin American countries), etc. It is a popular name; for example, in 1968, it was the 14th most frequently-given name for girls in the United States
